  "stimulus": "The function $f$ is defined on the closed interval $[-5, 4]$. The graph of $f$ consists of three line segments. Let $g$ be the function defined by $g(x) = \\int_{-3}^x f(t)\\, dt$.",
  "stimulus_image": null,
  "documents": null,
  "parts": [
    {
      "letter": "a",
      "prompt": "Find $g(3)$.",
      "point_value": 1,
      "scoring_notes": "From scoring key: $g(3) = \\int_{-3}^3 f(t)\\, dt = 9$ (computed via signed areas of the three line segments).",
      "requires_drawing": false,
      "reference_image": null,
      "scoring_points": [
        {
          "point_id": "a1",
          "point_value": 1,
          "description": "Correct answer using geometric areas",
          "alternatives": [
            {
              "required_elements": [
                "Correct answer using geometric areas"
              ],
              "correct_example": "$g(3) = \\int_{-3}^3 f(t)\\, dt = 6 + 4 - 1 = 9$ (from graph geometry)"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "letter": "b",
      "prompt": "On what open intervals contained in $-5 < x < 4$ is the graph of $g$ both increasing and concave down? Give a reason for your answer.",
      "point_value": 2,
      "scoring_notes": "From scoring key: $g'(x) = f(x)$. $g$ is increasing and concave down on $(-5,-3)$ and $(0,2)$ because $f$ is positive and decreasing on these intervals.",
      "requires_drawing": false,
      "reference_image": null,
      "scoring_points": [
        {
          "point_id": "b1",
          "point_value": 1,
          "description": "Correct intervals",
          "alternatives": [
            {
              "required_elements": [
                "Correct intervals"
              ],
              "correct_example": "$(-5, -3)$ and $(0, 2)$"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "point_id": "b2",
          "point_value": 1,
          "description": "Reason",
          "alternatives": [
            {
              "required_elements": [
                "Reason"
              ],
              "correct_example": "$g'(x) = f(x)$; $g$ is increasing and concave down where $f$ is positive and decreasing"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "letter": "c",
      "prompt": "The function $h$ is defined by $h(x) = \\frac{g(x)}{5x}$. Find $h'(3)$.",
      "point_value": 3,
      "scoring_notes": "From scoring key: $h'(3) = \\frac{15(-2) - 5(9)}{225} = \\frac{-75}{225} = -\\frac{1}{3}$.",
      "requires_drawing": false,
      "reference_image": null,
      "scoring_points": [
        {
          "point_id": "c1",
          "point_value": 1,
          "description": "Applies quotient rule",
          "alternatives": [
            {
              "required_elements": [
                "Applies quotient rule"
              ],
              "correct_example": "$h'(x) = \\frac{5x \\cdot g'(x) - g(x) \\cdot 5}{(5x)^2} = \\frac{5x g'(x) - 5g(x)}{25x^2}$"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "point_id": "c2",
          "point_value": 1,
          "description": "Substitutes values",
          "alternatives": [
            {
              "required_elements": [
                "Substitutes values"
              ],
              "correct_example": "$g'(3) = f(3) = -2$, $g(3) = 9$"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "point_id": "c3",
          "point_value": 1,
          "description": "Correct answer",
          "alternatives": [
            {
              "required_elements": [
                "Correct answer"
              ],
              "correct_example": "$h'(3) = \\frac{5(3)(-2) - 5(9)}{25(9)} = \\frac{-30 - 45}{225} = \\frac{-75}{225} = -\\frac{1}{3}$"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "letter": "d",
      "prompt": "The function $p$ is defined by $p(x) = f(x^2 - x)$. Find the slope of the line tangent to the graph of $p$ at the point where $x = -1$.",
      "point_value": 3,
      "scoring_notes": "From scoring key: $p'(-1) = f'(x^2-x) \\cdot (2x-1)\\big|_{x=-1} = f'(2)(-3) = (-2)(-3) = 6$.",
      "requires_drawing": false,
      "reference_image": null,
      "scoring_points": [
        {
          "point_id": "d1",
